@page "/typography"

<PageTitle>Typography - Quark Suite</PageTitle>

<Div Space="Space.Y.Is8" MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Is4xl">
    <Div Space="Space.Y.Is4">
        <DemoSection Description="The shadcn typography article example." Code="@TypographyDemoCode" CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Div>
                <h1 class="scroll-m-20 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-balance">
                    Taxing Laughter: The Joke Tax Chronicles
                </h1>
                <p class="text-xl leading-7 text-muted-foreground [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-6">
                    Once upon a time, in a far-off land, there was a very lazy king who spent all day lounging on his throne.
                    One day, his advisors came to him with a problem: the kingdom was running out of money.
                </p>
                <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight transition-colors first:mt-0">
                    The King's Plan
                </h2>
                <p class="leading-7 [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-6">
                    The king thought long and hard, and finally came up with
                    <a href="#" class="font-medium text-primary underline underline-offset-4">a brilliant plan</a>:
                    he would tax the jokes in the kingdom.
                </p>
                <blockquote class="mt-6 border-l-2 pl-6 italic">
                    "After all," he said, "everyone enjoys a good joke, so it's only fair that they should pay for the privilege."
                </blockquote>
                <h3 class="mt-8 scroll-m-20 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">The Joke Tax</h3>
                <p class="leading-7 [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-6">
                    The king's subjects were not amused. They grumbled and complained, but the king was firm:
                </p>
                <ul class="my-6 ml-6 list-disc [&>li]:mt-2">
                    <li>1st level of puns: 5 gold coins</li>
                    <li>2nd level of jokes: 10 gold coins</li>
                    <li>3rd level of one-liners : 20 gold coins</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="leading-7 [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-6">
                    As a result, people stopped telling jokes, and the kingdom fell into a gloom. But there was one person who
                    refused to let the king's foolishness get him down: a court jester named Jokester.
                </p>
                <h3 class="mt-8 scroll-m-20 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Jokester's Revolt</h3>
                <p class="leading-7 [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-6">
                    Jokester began sneaking into the castle in the middle of the night and leaving jokes all over the place:
                    under the king's pillow, in his soup, even in the royal toilet. The king was furious, but he couldn't seem to
                    stop Jokester.
                </p>
                <p class="leading-7 [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-6">
                    And then, one day, the people of the kingdom discovered that the jokes left by Jokester were so funny that
                    they couldn't help but laugh. And once they started laughing, they couldn't stop.
                </p>
                <h3 class="mt-8 scroll-m-20 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">The People's Rebellion</h3>
                <p class="leading-7 [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-6">
                    The people of the kingdom, feeling uplifted by the laughter, started to tell jokes and puns again, and soon
                    the entire kingdom was in on the joke.
                </p>
                <div class="my-6 w-full overflow-y-auto">
                    <table class="w-full">
                        <thead>
                        <tr class="m-0 border-t p-0 even:bg-muted">
                            <th class="border px-4 py-2 text-left font-bold [&[align=center]]:text-center [&[align=right]]:text-right">King's Treasury</th>
                            <th class="border px-4 py-2 text-left font-bold [&[align=center]]:text-center [&[align=right]]:text-right">People's happiness</th>
                        </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                        <tr class="m-0 border-t p-0 even:bg-muted">
                            <td class="border px-4 py-2 text-left [&[align=center]]:text-center [&[align=right]]:text-right">Empty</td>
                            <td class="border px-4 py-2 text-left [&[align=center]]:text-center [&[align=right]]:text-right">Overflowing</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="m-0 border-t p-0 even:bg-muted">
                            <td class="border px-4 py-2 text-left [&[align=center]]:text-center [&[align=right]]:text-right">Modest</td>
                            <td class="border px-4 py-2 text-left [&[align=center]]:text-center [&[align=right]]:text-right">Satisfied</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="m-0 border-t p-0 even:bg-muted">
                            <td class="border px-4 py-2 text-left [&[align=center]]:text-center [&[align=right]]:text-right">Full</td>
                            <td class="border px-4 py-2 text-left [&[align=center]]:text-center [&[align=right]]:text-right">Ecstatic</td>
                        </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <p class="leading-7 [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-6">
                    The king, seeing how much happier his subjects were, realized the error of his ways and repealed the joke tax.
                    Jokester was declared a hero, and the kingdom lived happily ever after.
                </p>
                <p class="leading-7 [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-6">
                    The moral of the story is: never underestimate the power of a good laugh and always be careful of bad ideas.
                </p>
            </Div>
            </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="h1" Description="Text on H1-H6 using semantic and Tailwind palette tokens." Code="@(@"<H4 TextColor=""TextColor.Primary"">Primary</H4>
<H4 TextColor=""TextColor.Accent"">Accent</H4>
<H4 TextColor=""TextColor.Token(""amber-600"")"">Amber</H4>")"
CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Div Display="Display.Flex" FlexWrap="FlexWrap.Wrap" Gap="Gap.Is4.Column.Is2.Row">
                <H4 TextColor="TextColor.Primary" Margin="Margin.Is0">Primary</H4>
                <H4 TextColor="TextColor.Accent" Margin="Margin.Is0">Accent</H4>
                <H4 TextColor='TextColor.Token("amber-600")' Margin="Margin.Is0">Amber</H4>
                <H4 TextColor="TextColor.Destructive" Margin="Margin.Is0">Destructive</H4>
                <H4 TextColor='TextColor.Token("sky-600")' Margin="Margin.Is0">Sky</H4>
            </Div>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="h2" Description="Text with Text for semantic styling." Code="@(@"<Text>Regular text</Text>
<Text TextColor=""TextColor.Primary"">Primary text</Text>
<Text TextColor=""TextColor.Accent"">Accent text</Text>
<Text TextColor=""TextColor.Destructive"">Destructive text</Text>")"
CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Div Space="Space.Y.Is2">
                <Text>Regular text element.</Text>
                <Text TextColor="TextColor.Primary">Primary text.</Text>
                <Text TextColor="TextColor.Accent">Accent text.</Text>
                <Text TextColor="TextColor.Destructive">Destructive text.</Text>
            </Div>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="h3" Description="Text size variations." Code="@(@"<Text TextSize=""TextSize.Sm"" Display=""Display.Block"">Small text</Text>
<Text Display=""Display.Block"">Default text</Text>
<Text TextSize=""TextSize.Lg"" Display=""Display.Block"">Large text</Text>")"
CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Div Space="Space.Y.Is1">
                <Text TextSize="TextSize.Sm" Display="Display.Block">Small text</Text>
                <Text Display="Display.Block">Default text</Text>
                <Text TextSize="TextSize.Lg" Display="Display.Block">Large text</Text>
                <Text TextSize="TextSize.Xl" Display="Display.Block">Extra Large text</Text>
            </Div>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="h4" Description="Strong, em, Small, underlined, strikethrough." Code="@(@"<Strong>Strong (bold)</Strong>
<Text><em>Italic using em</em></Text>
<Small>Small text</Small>
<Text><u>Underlined</u></Text>")"
CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Div Space="Space.Y.Is1">
                <Strong>Strong (bold)</Strong>
                <Text Display="Display.Block"><em>Italic using em</em></Text>
                <Small Display="Display.Block">Small text</Small>
                <Text Display="Display.Block"><u>Underlined</u></Text>
                <Text Display="Display.Block"><s>Strikethrough</s></Text>
            </Div>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="p" Description="Blockquotes are useful for callouts, testimonials, and cited notes." Code="@(@"<Blockquote TextColor=""TextColor.MutedForeground"">Quoted text</Blockquote>")"
        CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Blockquote TextColor="TextColor.MutedForeground">
                "After moving the dashboard to Quark, the whole team could ship UI changes faster."
            </Blockquote>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="blockquote" Description="Inline Code and PreCode blocks." Code="@(@"<Code>Inline code</Code>
<PreCode Class=""block"">Code block\nPreserves formatting</PreCode>
<Code TextColor=""TextColor.Destructive"">Error: 404</Code>")"
CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Div Space="Space.Y.Is2">
                <Code>Inline code</Code>
                <PreCode Display="Display.Block">@("Code block\nPreserves formatting")</PreCode>
                <Code TextColor="TextColor.Destructive">Error: 404</Code>
            </Div>
        </DemoSection>

        <Div Display="Display.Grid" Gap='Gap.Token("6")' Class="md:grid-cols-2">
            <DemoSection Title="table" Code="@(@"<UnorderedList>
    <UnorderedListItem>First item</UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem>Second item</UnorderedListItem>
</UnorderedList>")"
CodeLanguage="razor">
                <UnorderedList>
                    <UnorderedListItem>First item</UnorderedListItem>
                    <UnorderedListItem>Second item</UnorderedListItem>
                    <UnorderedListItem>Third item</UnorderedListItem>
                </UnorderedList>
            </DemoSection>
            <DemoSection Title="list" Code="@(@"<OrderedList>
    <OrderedListItem>First numbered item</OrderedListItem>
    <OrderedListItem>Second numbered item</OrderedListItem>
</OrderedList>")"
CodeLanguage="razor">
                <OrderedList>
                    <OrderedListItem>First numbered item</OrderedListItem>
                    <OrderedListItem>Second numbered item</OrderedListItem>
                    <OrderedListItem>Third numbered item</OrderedListItem>
                </OrderedList>
            </DemoSection>
        </Div>

        <DemoSection Title="Inline code" Description="Use regular semantic tables for dense, structured content." Code="@(@"<TableElement><Thead>...</Thead><Tbody>...</Tbody></TableElement>")"
        CodeLanguage="razor">
            <TableElement>
                <Thead>
                    <Tr>
                        <Th>Plan</Th>
                        <Th>Seats</Th>
                        <Th>Price</Th>
                    </Tr>
                </Thead>
                <Tbody>
                    <Tr>
                        <Td>Starter</Td>
                        <Td>3</Td>
                        <Td>$9</Td>
                    </Tr>
                    <Tr>
                        <Td>Team</Td>
                        <Td>10</Td>
                        <Td>$29</Td>
                    </Tr>
                </Tbody>
            </TableElement>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="Lead" Description="Br and Hr components." Code="@(@"<Text>First line.</Text>
<Br/>
<Text>Second line after break.</Text>
<Hr/>
<Text>Content below horizontal rule.</Text>")"
CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Text>First line.</Text>
            <Br/>
            <Text>Second line after break.</Text>
            <Hr/>
            <Text>Content below horizontal rule.</Text>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="Large" Description="TextTransform, FontWeight, FontStyle on Text." Code="@(@"<Text TextTransform=""TextTransform.Uppercase"" Display=""Display.Block"">uppercase</Text>
<Text TextTransform=""TextTransform.Lowercase"" Display=""Display.Block"">LOWERCASE</Text>
<Text FontWeight=""FontWeight.Bold"" Display=""Display.Block"">Bold</Text>
<Text FontStyle=""FontStyle.Italic"" Display=""Display.Block"">Italic</Text>")"
CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Div Space="Space.Y.Is1">
                <Text TextTransform="TextTransform.Uppercase" Display="Display.Block">uppercase</Text>
                <Text TextTransform="TextTransform.Lowercase" Display="Display.Block">LOWERCASE</Text>
                <Text FontWeight="FontWeight.Bold" Display="Display.Block">Bold</Text>
                <Text FontStyle="FontStyle.Italic" Display="Display.Block">Italic</Text>
            </Div>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="Small" Description="Lead copy should feel more prominent than body copy without becoming a heading." Code="@(@"<Lead>Lead paragraph</Lead>")"
        CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Lead>Ship composable UI primitives faster with a design system that still feels native to Blazor.</Lead>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="Muted" Description="Large supporting text helps introduce sections or summarize the next block of content." Code="@(@"<Text TextSize=""TextSize.Lg"">Large text</Text>")"
        CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Text TextSize="TextSize.Lg">This workspace contains all the tools needed to assemble a modern product dashboard.</Text>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="RTL" Description="Muted text is useful for secondary metadata and subtle helper copy." Code="@(@"<Muted>Muted text</Muted>")"
        CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Muted>Last synced 3 minutes ago from the production region.</Muted>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="Display Headings" Description="DisplaySize on H1–H3 for large display text." Code="@(@"<H1 DisplaySize=""DisplaySize.Is1"">Display 1</H1>
<H2 DisplaySize=""DisplaySize.Is2"">Display 2</H2>
<H3 DisplaySize=""DisplaySize.Is3"">Display 3</H3>")"
CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Div Space="Space.Y.Is1">
                <H1 DisplaySize="DisplaySize.Is1">Display 1</H1>
                <H2 DisplaySize="DisplaySize.Is2">Display 2</H2>
                <H3 DisplaySize="DisplaySize.Is3">Display 3</H3>
            </Div>
        </DemoSection>

        <DemoSection Title="RTL" Description="Typography should remain readable and well-spaced in right-to-left layouts too." Code="@(@"<Div dir=""rtl"" Space=""Space.Y.Is2"" TextAlign=""TextAlign.End""><H4>مرحبا</H4><Paragraph>RTL sample text.</Paragraph></Div>")"
        CodeLanguage="razor">
            <Div dir="rtl" Space="Space.Y.Is2" TextAlign="TextAlign.End">
                <H4>مرحبا بكم في كوارك</H4>
                <Paragraph>هذا مثال بسيط يوضح كيف تبدو المسافات والمحاذاة في اتجاه من اليمين إلى اليسار.</Paragraph>
            </Div>
        </DemoSection>
    </Div>
</Div>

@code {
    private const string TypographyDemoCode =
@"<div>
  <h1 class=""scroll-m-20 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-balance"">
    Taxing Laughter: The Joke Tax Chronicles
  </h1>
  <p class=""text-xl leading-7 text-muted-foreground [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-6"">
    Once upon a time, in a far-off land, there was a very lazy king who spent all day lounging on his throne.
  </p>
  <h2 class=""mt-10 scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight transition-colors first:mt-0"">
    The King's Plan
  </h2>
  <p class=""leading-7 [&:not(:first-child)]:mt-6"">The king thought long and hard...</p>
